This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with understanding the underlying ontology behind Google's semantic search feature. It also involves the analysis of a large dataset and the use of classification systems, which are common topics in the Information Retrieval field. 

The paper also touches upon Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the Google Knowledge Graph, which is a key component of Google's AI-powered search engine. 

The use of RDF triples and linked data technology suggests that the paper may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on ontology and classification systems also makes it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's analysis of language and concepts may also place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
